#X obj 83 120 else/mono~, f 22;
#X text 364 494 0: always random (default);
#X text 364 512 1: initially random;
#X text 364 532 2: fixed based on golden ratios;
#X text 364 551 3: all locked to 0;
#X text 347 284 The rightmost inlet takes impulses to sync all the 7 oscillators. By default (mode 0) \, it generates a random phase for each. In mode 1 we have an initial random value and we sync to this same random setting every time. Mode 2 syncs to a fixed and deterministic list of phases based on the golden ratio. Mode 4 resets all phases to 0 \, which makes it sound quite flangy., f 34;
